import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    airport_count = data.groupby('airport')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    airport_count = airport_count.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=airport_count)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby('date').sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axvline(data['date'].min(), color='red', label=f"Min date: {data['date'].min().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    chart.axvline(data['date'].max(), color='green', label=f"Max date: {data['date'].max().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')}")
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
